WEBVTT

00:00.290 --> 00:01.620
Bex:
<i>Previously on </i>Andi Mack...

00:01.620 --> 00:04.120
-My parents are
getting married.
-Cool!

00:04.120 --> 00:05.290
When's the big day?

00:05.290 --> 00:07.000
-We haven't gotten
that far, yet.
-No.

00:07.000 --> 00:08.460
Bex:
We can just get
married at City Hall.

00:08.460 --> 00:09.960
There's gonna be a wedding.

00:09.960 --> 00:11.380
Maid of honor, ready to go.

00:11.380 --> 00:13.250
I have come to take
you cake tasting.

00:13.250 --> 00:14.330
Who could say
no to that?

00:14.330 --> 00:15.289
The bride.

00:15.289 --> 00:17.289
Well, it's her loss.

00:17.289 --> 00:19.120
My dad passed away
three years ago.

00:19.120 --> 00:20.750
Bowie,
I'm so sorry.

00:20.750 --> 00:22.120
You may not have your dad,

00:22.120 --> 00:23.960
<i>but you do have a daughter.</i>

00:24.879 --> 00:25.920
Did you hear that?

00:25.920 --> 00:27.579
I just turned
into my dad.

00:27.579 --> 00:28.579
Actually...

00:28.579 --> 00:31.879
I think you just
turned into my dad.

00:31.879 --> 00:33.920
It's been way too long
since we've hung out.

00:33.920 --> 00:35.789
I have plans
tomorrow night.

00:35.789 --> 00:37.079
With who?

00:37.079 --> 00:38.750
Andi:
<i>Amber's taking me to a party.</i>

00:38.750 --> 00:40.039
<i>I'm sure you can come!</i>

00:40.039 --> 00:42.789
Buffy:
<i>I don't want to tag along
to a party I wasn't invited to.</i>

00:42.789 --> 00:44.119
♪ ♪

00:44.119 --> 00:45.619
Hey!

00:45.619 --> 00:47.789
I was hoping that...

00:47.789 --> 00:50.380
dance dance film festival
was still happening?

00:50.380 --> 00:52.250
That'll be going on
all night.

00:58.619 --> 01:00.329
Cyrus:
I find this odd.

01:00.329 --> 01:01.789
Very odd.

01:01.789 --> 01:04.579
I wouldn't say "very."

01:04.579 --> 01:06.670
I would say "extremely" odd.

01:06.670 --> 01:08.250
(door closes)

01:08.920 --> 01:10.460
Jonah:
So...

01:10.460 --> 01:12.420
what's all this about?

01:12.420 --> 01:14.250
You have something to tell us?

01:14.250 --> 01:16.829
You know that Jefferson
has a Secret Society?

01:19.250 --> 01:21.079
You've never heard
about the Secret Society?

01:21.079 --> 01:22.670
-Nothing.
-No.

01:22.670 --> 01:24.120
They're that good.

01:24.120 --> 01:25.420
Are you part of it?

01:25.420 --> 01:26.920
That's not important.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.750
-He's part of it!
-Jonah: Shhh!

01:28.750 --> 01:30.960
Please! The Secret Society
doesn't know that I'm here.

01:30.960 --> 01:32.250
Or do they?

01:32.250 --> 01:34.329
(eerie music)

01:36.379 --> 01:38.289
One of you is going
to be invited to join.

01:38.289 --> 01:39.620
Which one?

01:39.620 --> 01:41.710
I don't know.
I shouldn't even
be telling you this,

01:41.710 --> 01:44.500
-but I wanted you
to be prepared.
-For what?

01:46.210 --> 01:47.920
You'll get a note,

01:47.920 --> 01:50.750
a plain piece of paper,
and all it says is:

01:50.750 --> 01:51.579
"Will you?"

01:52.879 --> 01:54.379
But they only
want one of us?

01:54.879 --> 01:57.079
Well, if the Secret Society
wants one of us,

01:57.079 --> 01:58.670
they have to take
all of us.

01:58.670 --> 02:00.209
That's not how it works.

02:00.209 --> 02:02.379
If they ask me, I'll say no.

02:02.379 --> 02:03.540
Me, too.

02:03.540 --> 02:05.540
We all know they're
not going to ask me.

02:15.960 --> 02:17.670
"Will you?"

02:17.670 --> 02:18.750
"Will you" what?

02:18.750 --> 02:20.420
Oh, I can't tell you.

02:20.420 --> 02:22.079
It's the Secret Society.

02:22.079 --> 02:23.079
They want me.

02:25.079 --> 02:26.039
Oops.

02:27.170 --> 02:30.670
<i>♪ I'm standin'
on the edge ♪</i>

02:30.670 --> 02:35.039
<i>♪ And everything I know-oh-oh
is blown away ♪</i>

02:36.960 --> 02:39.120
<i>♪ Life is upside down ♪</i>

02:40.039 --> 02:44.210
<i>♪ But any way it goes
I'll work it out ♪</i>

02:46.420 --> 02:49.750
<i>♪ Oh oh oh oh oh ♪</i>

02:49.750 --> 02:52.210
<i>♪ Here we go ♪</i>

02:53.620 --> 02:56.420
<i>-♪ One, two, three ♪
-♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪</i>

02:56.420 --> 02:59.079
<i>♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪</i>

02:59.079 --> 03:01.500
<i>♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪</i>

03:01.500 --> 03:03.750
<i>♪ But I'm with you all the way ♪</i>

03:03.750 --> 03:06.289
<i>♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪</i>

03:06.289 --> 03:08.620
<i>-♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪
-♪ Hey ♪</i>

03:08.620 --> 03:10.960
<i>♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪</i>

03:10.960 --> 03:13.919
<i>-♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪
-♪ Hey ♪</i>

03:13.919 --> 03:15.960
<i>♪ All the way ♪</i>

03:15.960 --> 03:18.120
♪ ♪

03:22.329 --> 03:24.579
(clears throat)

03:25.500 --> 03:26.960
Hey.

03:28.329 --> 03:29.789
What'd you think?

03:29.789 --> 03:30.829
About what?

03:31.620 --> 03:32.960
Bex!

03:32.960 --> 03:35.460
You need me to tell you
you look incredible?

03:35.460 --> 03:36.789
Yes!

03:36.789 --> 03:37.879
Okay.

03:37.879 --> 03:39.210
Well...

03:39.210 --> 03:41.829
considering you look
pretty great every day...

03:41.829 --> 03:44.210
at this moment, you are...

03:45.250 --> 03:46.289
so beautiful.

03:48.420 --> 03:50.170
I can't believe
I get to marry you.

03:51.920 --> 03:53.460
You can't just come in
the kitchen looking like that,

03:53.460 --> 03:54.579
I'm only human.

03:54.579 --> 03:56.120
Well, that's more like it.

03:56.120 --> 03:58.079
(Bex giggles)

03:58.079 --> 03:59.079
Wow...

03:59.079 --> 04:01.039
Great tuxedo.

04:01.039 --> 04:02.539
Where did you get it?

04:02.539 --> 04:04.289
It was my dad's.

04:04.289 --> 04:05.669
The one he wore
at his wedding.

04:05.669 --> 04:08.620
You're gonna marry me
in your dad's tuxedo?

04:10.000 --> 04:12.750
I know you can't show
me your dress, but...

04:12.750 --> 04:14.039
have you picked
one out yet?

04:16.079 --> 04:17.620
Mm-hmm...

04:21.120 --> 04:22.379
Where's your
wedding dress?

04:23.329 --> 04:24.750
I know I have it.

04:24.750 --> 04:26.250
It's in a white garment bag.

04:26.250 --> 04:27.709
Go check upstairs
in the closet.

04:30.079 --> 04:31.329
Bex:
Found it!

04:31.329 --> 04:33.420
Bowie is going to wear
his father's tuxedo
to the wedding

04:33.420 --> 04:34.829
so I thought what if...

04:34.829 --> 04:35.959
Then this happened.

04:35.959 --> 04:38.620
-I was small.
-Bex: Well I'm not!

04:38.620 --> 04:41.620
I'm a hulking behemoth
who now needs to buy
a wedding dress.

04:41.620 --> 04:42.670
Ah!

04:43.120 --> 04:46.040
I have been preparing
for this moment!

04:46.040 --> 04:47.540
-(grunts)
-Whoa.

04:47.540 --> 04:49.040
Wait, there's more!

04:49.040 --> 04:50.379
(straining)

04:53.379 --> 04:55.000
Whoa.

04:55.000 --> 04:56.750
♪ ♪

04:57.709 --> 04:58.620
Cyrus:
Don't get me wrong.

04:58.620 --> 05:00.040
I'm still
extremely opposed

05:00.040 --> 05:02.209
to the entire concept
of a Secret Society--

05:02.209 --> 05:03.120
You want to go.

05:03.120 --> 05:04.670
Not to join.

05:04.670 --> 05:07.170
For research
purposes only.

05:08.379 --> 05:10.579
I think that's
a good idea.

05:10.579 --> 05:12.459
He checks it out,
comes back,

05:12.459 --> 05:13.920
and spills the beans.

05:13.920 --> 05:15.500
That would be
my sole purpose--

05:15.500 --> 05:16.879
Bean spilling.

05:16.879 --> 05:20.459
And then the Secret Society
won't be so secret.

05:20.459 --> 05:22.670
But I thought we agreed
we were gonna say no.

05:22.670 --> 05:25.329
Yeah, but then I got invited.

05:25.329 --> 05:27.750
You seem a little
too excited that
they picked you.

05:27.750 --> 05:29.329
I'm not a little excited,

05:29.329 --> 05:30.670
I'm ecstatic!

05:32.079 --> 05:34.829
Buffy. We can trust him.
He'll do what he says.

05:34.829 --> 05:36.540
He'll see
what it's about,

05:36.540 --> 05:38.829
and then he'll
tell us everything.

05:38.829 --> 05:42.620
♪ ♪

05:42.620 --> 05:44.879
Ooh, do you like
this one?

05:44.879 --> 05:46.579
(gasps)
How 'bout this one?

05:50.250 --> 05:52.540
Oh, how 'bout that one?

05:53.879 --> 05:55.120
You aren't one of those
people who can sleep

05:55.120 --> 05:56.670
with their eyes
open, are you?

05:56.670 --> 05:58.709
(snores)

05:58.709 --> 06:03.420
You haven't seen one dress,
not one, that you like at all?

06:03.420 --> 06:07.329
Can you get snow blindness
from staring at too many
white dresses?

06:08.329 --> 06:10.250
Do we have
to keep doing this?

06:12.750 --> 06:14.379
Well, we could
go to a store.

06:14.379 --> 06:15.790
You could try
some dresses on

06:15.790 --> 06:17.459
like the cave woman
brides used to do.

06:18.209 --> 06:19.459
I know you can't tell
because of the eye drops,

06:19.459 --> 06:20.579
but these are
grateful tears.

06:21.829 --> 06:22.959
Oh, yeah.

06:23.500 --> 06:24.540
Oh.

06:25.620 --> 06:28.379
So, you joined
the Secret Society.

06:28.379 --> 06:29.500
That's what
you're saying?

06:29.500 --> 06:31.540
No, I'm not saying that.

06:31.540 --> 06:33.120
Then, what are
you saying?

06:33.959 --> 06:35.709
Nothing.

06:35.709 --> 06:38.170
Because there is
no Secret Society.

06:38.170 --> 06:40.420
Oh, we're doing
that now.

06:42.920 --> 06:44.670
What is your role
in all of this?

06:44.670 --> 06:46.120
Are you his handler
or something?

06:46.120 --> 06:48.209
You have to make sure
he doesn't say anything?

06:48.209 --> 06:51.040
No! I-I thought we were...

06:51.040 --> 06:53.750
um, going to get ice cream.

06:53.750 --> 06:55.920
Has anyone ever told you
you should be an actor?

06:55.920 --> 06:58.290
Andi:
You promised
you'd tell us.

06:58.290 --> 07:00.620
And we believed you.

07:00.620 --> 07:02.250
One of us
believed you.

07:02.250 --> 07:05.209
I feel like you're
picking the Secret
Society over us.

07:05.209 --> 07:06.920
What do they have
that we don't?

07:06.920 --> 07:09.709
Cyrus! We've said
all we can.

07:09.709 --> 07:11.879
Let's go. We have to...

07:13.620 --> 07:14.829
you know.

07:14.829 --> 07:16.290
Yeah.

07:18.500 --> 07:20.500
Well, we have to...

07:20.500 --> 07:22.879
"you know," too!

07:27.040 --> 07:30.329
<i>♪ Let it into your heart ♪</i>

07:31.620 --> 07:36.170
<i>♪ Always follow who you are ♪</i>

07:36.170 --> 07:37.750
<i>♪ Come to life ♪</i>

07:40.079 --> 07:44.790
<i>♪ Come to life, come to life ♪</i>

07:44.790 --> 07:47.670
<i>-♪ Come to life... ♪
</i>-Don't worry, we have
plenty of them.

07:47.670 --> 07:53.040
<i>♪ Come to life, come to life ♪</i>

07:54.209 --> 07:58.790
<i>♪ Let it into your heart ♪</i>

07:58.790 --> 08:03.079
<i>♪ Always follow who you are ♪</i>

08:03.079 --> 08:04.500
<i>♪ Come to life ♪</i>

08:07.000 --> 08:08.329
I love it.

08:08.329 --> 08:09.250
You do?

08:10.250 --> 08:11.379
She loves it!

08:11.379 --> 08:12.500
Don't you?

08:12.500 --> 08:13.829
I guess...

08:13.829 --> 08:15.790
Celia:
It's gorgeous!

08:18.879 --> 08:21.040
Aw, Bex...

08:21.040 --> 08:22.290
this is the one.

08:23.620 --> 08:25.000
But what do you think?

08:26.420 --> 08:28.500
I wish Andi were here.

08:29.959 --> 08:32.120
-Both: Andi!
-I'm sorry, who's Andi?

08:32.120 --> 08:33.000
My daughter.

08:33.000 --> 08:34.120
Should we give her a call?

08:34.120 --> 08:35.250
Celia and Bex:
No!

08:35.250 --> 08:37.289
She has to be
part of picking out
the dress.

08:37.289 --> 08:39.789
She can't know we went
shopping without her.

08:39.789 --> 08:41.120
Can you hold it for a day,

08:41.120 --> 08:42.879
and we'll just come back
tomorrow and do it again?

08:42.879 --> 08:44.830
I'm sorry, we don't hold
sale items.

08:44.830 --> 08:45.960
It's on sale?

08:45.960 --> 08:47.500
25% off.

08:47.500 --> 08:49.960
I just fell in love with it
all over again.

08:49.960 --> 08:51.919
♪ ♪

08:54.120 --> 08:57.419
(New Orleans jazz music)

08:57.419 --> 08:59.539
-That's--
-Isn't it?

09:07.830 --> 09:08.750
Can I change now?

09:08.750 --> 09:09.750
One more time.

09:09.750 --> 09:11.120
And move your arms more.

09:11.120 --> 09:12.419
Yeah, like a human.

09:12.419 --> 09:14.039
How's this?

09:14.039 --> 09:16.210
Bye. I'm done.

09:19.120 --> 09:20.330
Do you see
my problem?

09:21.750 --> 09:22.620
No.

09:22.620 --> 09:25.710
The groom cannot be more
beautiful than the bride.

09:25.710 --> 09:27.330
How am I gonna find
a dress that measures
up to that?

09:27.330 --> 09:29.000
It's a lot of pressure.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.169
That's not the answer
I was looking for.

09:31.169 --> 09:32.120
Will you help me?

09:32.120 --> 09:34.580
Of course!
When can we start?

09:34.580 --> 09:36.080
How about after school?

09:36.080 --> 09:40.620
Yay! I can't wait to see
the look on your face
when we find the one.

09:41.580 --> 09:42.620
Are you guys talking about me?

09:42.620 --> 09:44.830
-No!
-The dress!

09:44.830 --> 09:47.460
I don't have a limitless
supply of self-esteem.

09:48.379 --> 09:49.289
Oh!

09:49.289 --> 09:51.419
We cannot forget
to invite CeCe.

09:51.419 --> 09:54.000
Oh, right! It would be
terrible to leave her out.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.789
And she has the credit card.

09:55.789 --> 09:57.330
♪ ♪

10:02.120 --> 10:04.500
The point is,
it doesn't change
anything between us.

10:04.500 --> 10:06.210
Cyrus, it's fine.

10:06.210 --> 10:07.879
I really don't care.

10:07.879 --> 10:10.710
I have less than
zero interest in
the Secret Society.

10:11.580 --> 10:14.379
♪ ♪

10:20.460 --> 10:23.039
Do you need me to
replay the sentence
you just said?

10:23.039 --> 10:24.289
No!

10:24.289 --> 10:26.539
So... will you?

10:27.669 --> 10:31.419
I don't know, if Cyrus isn't
going to tell us anything,
then I--

10:31.419 --> 10:33.120
Save it!

10:33.120 --> 10:35.330
I'll see you
on the flip side.

10:38.289 --> 10:39.919
(squeals)

10:43.120 --> 10:45.750
I can't tell you
anything.

10:45.750 --> 10:47.250
I'm really sorry.

10:47.250 --> 10:50.120
-You don't
have to apologize.
-Cyrus!

10:50.120 --> 10:52.669
I'm going to apologize
if I want to apologize.

10:52.669 --> 10:54.419
It's okay.

10:55.710 --> 10:58.000
I knew this is
what would happen.

10:58.000 --> 11:00.460
No... Buffy!

11:04.830 --> 11:05.669
(slams book down)

11:07.330 --> 11:08.960
That was excruciating.

11:11.379 --> 11:15.830
Oh, I gotta go, I get to go
wedding dress shopping
with my mom.

11:15.830 --> 11:17.879
Oh, that should be fun.

11:17.879 --> 11:21.169
(sighs)
Yeah, I could use
a little of that right now.

11:28.789 --> 11:29.710
How'd she do?

11:29.710 --> 11:32.080
It's tough at first.
She's a newbie.

11:32.080 --> 11:33.710
Which you were yesterday.

11:33.710 --> 11:36.669
Yeah, but yesterday I didn't
have someone to lord it over.

11:36.669 --> 11:38.289
♪ ♪

11:41.750 --> 11:43.750
What if I found
something today?

11:43.750 --> 11:45.460
Oh, don't be
ridiculous.

11:45.460 --> 11:47.750
Nobody finds their
wedding dress that fast.

11:47.750 --> 11:50.039
Can I get anyone
something to drink?

11:50.039 --> 11:51.000
I'm Ricky,
by the way,

11:51.000 --> 11:51.960
I'll be helping
you today.

11:51.960 --> 11:53.710
Hi, Andi, the daughter.

11:53.710 --> 11:54.960
Celia, the mother.

11:54.960 --> 11:56.120
And Bex, the bride.

11:56.120 --> 11:58.580
Generation representation,
I love it!

11:58.580 --> 12:01.580
You know, there's a dress
that might be perfect...

12:02.919 --> 12:04.169
Let me show you.

12:07.379 --> 12:08.919
(gasps)

12:10.120 --> 12:11.539
It's beautiful.

12:11.539 --> 12:12.919
But, is it the one?

12:12.919 --> 12:15.580
Oh, you have to see it on!

12:15.580 --> 12:18.210
♪ ♪

12:26.710 --> 12:27.669
Mom...

12:30.750 --> 12:32.379
look at you...

12:32.379 --> 12:34.080
Do you like it?

12:35.580 --> 12:36.879
You're glowing!

12:36.879 --> 12:38.879
Absolutely!

12:38.879 --> 12:40.210
Well...

12:40.210 --> 12:42.250
put it in the "maybe" pile.

12:42.250 --> 12:43.919
And try on the next one.

12:43.919 --> 12:46.000
Do we really need to make piles?

12:46.000 --> 12:47.169
This is the dress!

12:48.210 --> 12:50.419
This is "a" dress.

12:50.419 --> 12:52.500
We get to see her in
a bunch of dresses.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.539
Isn't that the fun part?

12:54.539 --> 12:55.789
You know what else is fun?

12:56.539 --> 12:57.879
Finding the dress.

12:57.879 --> 13:00.250
Which I think she has.

13:00.250 --> 13:03.539
Well, her face didn't
even do the thing.

13:03.539 --> 13:04.379
What thing?

13:04.379 --> 13:07.000
You know, the...

13:07.000 --> 13:08.379
Ding!

13:08.379 --> 13:10.919
Oh, well, you said yourself.
She was glowing!

13:10.919 --> 13:12.789
She always glows.

13:12.789 --> 13:14.210
Ricky and Bex:
Awww.

13:14.210 --> 13:16.210
(scoffs)
I see plenty of ding.

13:16.210 --> 13:17.500
This is the dress!

13:19.289 --> 13:21.169
What do you keep saying that?

13:21.169 --> 13:23.620
"This is the dress"?

13:23.620 --> 13:26.000
What dress?

13:28.120 --> 13:30.580
The one we bought yesterday.

13:33.750 --> 13:35.879
I'll leave you ladies
to discuss.

13:40.750 --> 13:43.169
You went shopping yesterday?

13:44.169 --> 13:45.169
Yes...

13:45.169 --> 13:46.919
(scoffs)

13:46.919 --> 13:50.879
So I'm not here to help you
pick out your wedding dress.

13:52.250 --> 13:54.919
I'm here to watch
a reenactment

13:54.919 --> 13:56.830
of you picking out
your wedding dress?

13:56.830 --> 13:58.500
Oh, well, when you
put it that way--

13:58.500 --> 14:00.169
What other way
is there to put it?

14:00.169 --> 14:01.710
She is the bride.

14:01.710 --> 14:03.710
I know.

14:03.710 --> 14:07.000
Which means you get
to pick out any dress
you want.

14:07.830 --> 14:10.669
I just thought I was
gonna be a part of it...

14:11.379 --> 14:12.919
which I'm not.

14:16.120 --> 14:18.289
As the daughter
of the bride,

14:18.289 --> 14:21.000
I now pronounce
myself betrayed.

14:27.830 --> 14:31.120
Bex: Can we just stop with
all the hand-wringing
and the boo-hooing.

14:31.120 --> 14:32.210
It's over!

14:32.210 --> 14:34.289
I was able to
return the dress.

14:34.289 --> 14:36.419
I'm not boo-hooing,
okay?

14:36.419 --> 14:39.000
I just wanted to see
my mom's face

14:39.000 --> 14:41.000
when she found
her wedding dress.

14:42.169 --> 14:45.879
But if that's the dress
you love, you should
go back and get it.

14:45.879 --> 14:47.919
I just don't need
to be there

14:47.919 --> 14:49.580
when you find it
for the third time.

14:49.580 --> 14:52.620
I feel like I've looked
at every wedding dress
on this planet.

14:52.620 --> 14:55.620
-I don't think there is such
a thing as the perfect dress.
-There is!

14:57.460 --> 15:00.539
Bex:
What are the chances we're
gonna find a dress we all like?

15:02.620 --> 15:04.419
Mom!

15:04.419 --> 15:05.960
♪ ♪

15:16.500 --> 15:17.379
Ding.

15:20.580 --> 15:22.039
And ding.

15:32.539 --> 15:34.580
♪ ♪

15:45.460 --> 15:48.080
(locker closes)

15:48.080 --> 15:51.830
♪ ♪

16:04.379 --> 16:06.120
♪ ♪

16:12.750 --> 16:15.419
♪ ♪

16:19.539 --> 16:25.039
Hooded Figures: (chanting)
Will you? Will you?
Will you? Will you?

16:25.039 --> 16:28.120
Will you? Will you? Will you?

16:28.120 --> 16:30.500
This is so stupid.

16:30.500 --> 16:31.789
Will I what?

16:33.500 --> 16:35.330
Walker:
Will you go to my
Fall Formal with me?

16:37.210 --> 16:38.620
(in unison)
Surprise!

16:39.460 --> 16:40.960
What's going on?

16:40.960 --> 16:42.460
What is this?

16:42.460 --> 16:44.250
It's an epic prom-posal!

16:44.250 --> 16:46.379
Upon which all future
prom-posals will be measured.

16:46.379 --> 16:49.169
Andi:
Walker mapped out
this whole saga.

16:49.169 --> 16:50.879
You guys were great.

16:50.879 --> 16:53.169
I didn't like that we
couldn't say anything--

16:53.169 --> 16:55.120
But we had to make
it as mysterious
as possible.

16:55.120 --> 16:56.879
We found out
one at a time.

16:56.879 --> 16:58.210
Andi:
So, it wasn't that

16:58.210 --> 17:00.460
we chose the Secret
Society over you.

17:00.460 --> 17:02.919
We were pretending to
be the Secret Society
for you!

17:04.500 --> 17:07.710
So now that you know,
you aren't mad at us
anymore, right?

17:07.710 --> 17:09.960
I deserve all the blame.

17:09.960 --> 17:12.579
By which he clearly means
he deserve all the credit.

17:12.579 --> 17:15.119
Jonah: Look at her,
she's so stunned!

17:15.119 --> 17:16.619
She hasn't said anything!

17:16.619 --> 17:18.829
So, what's your answer?

17:18.829 --> 17:21.750
Will you go
to Fall Formal with me?

17:26.829 --> 17:28.619
No.

17:28.619 --> 17:31.539
♪ ♪

17:41.170 --> 17:42.210
Andi:
<i>Next on </i>Andi Mack...

17:42.210 --> 17:44.619
You guys really
thought I'd say yes?

17:44.619 --> 17:45.710
I feel bad
for the guy.

17:45.710 --> 17:47.079
His heart was
in the right place.

17:47.079 --> 17:49.750
And you still really
like him, right?

17:49.750 --> 17:51.329
-Eh...
-Hold up!

17:51.329 --> 17:53.539
Whoa, if you really
want this relationship
to end,

17:53.539 --> 17:55.750
you need to tell him
in person.

17:55.750 --> 17:57.250
What're you doing here?

17:57.250 --> 17:59.750
I'm supposed to come up
with an original dance for
my choreography final,

17:59.750 --> 18:01.380
<i>and perform it in
front of the class.</i>

18:01.380 --> 18:02.920
<i>I'll be your tutor.</i>

18:02.920 --> 18:04.750
<i>-Really You'd do that?
-Why not?</i>

18:04.750 --> 18:08.079
(quietly) Are you
still thinking about
breaking up with Jonah?

18:08.079 --> 18:09.539
Are you guys
talking about me?
